Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
writeDieAbstract(25.10)                                writeDieAbstract(25.10)

Name
       writeDieAbstract - Writes the abstract of current die to a file

Syntax
       writeDieAbstract

       <DIEABSTRACTFILE>

       [-noFilter]

       Writes  the  abstract  of current die to a file. It also writes the OBS
       for die edge checking to the die abstract file.  Specify  this  command
       after the initial floorplan is loaded. The file will be imported by the
       adjacent  die  and  therefore the current design will be honored by the
       adjacent die.

       This command supports the embedded bump flow for hierarchical designs.

       Note: By default, the proposed behavior for writeDieAbstract is:

              * For MACRO pin geometries, output ports on top metal  layer  in
                all MACROS of all classes.

              * For  routing,  output routing for all top level Verilog ports,
                and for power and ground, output only those wires with a SHAPE
                of IOWIRE.

Parameters
       <DIEABSTRACTFILE>
              Specifies the file name.

       -noFilter
              Turn off to filter the die abstract contents.

Examples
              * The following command creates a die abstract file die1.abs:

                writeDieAbstract die1.abs

Related Information
              * readDieAbstract

              * readTSVConfig

